76561198052772037,Not Recommended,259550,9115044,"Posted: 14 February, 2014",all,Kem Pet Unsu,"The only reason I say no is because it is not worth the price tag. You can clear the entire game, going for all achievements, in 3 hours. It's not a bad game, a little fun, but it's a very strictly linear game. No deviation from the storyline. No side quests, no way to change the ending, you just do a lot of clicking and searching for small, nearly-unnoticable items. It's kinda fun, and a way to kill time for a little bit, but if you see it and think it's a multiple playthrough game don't bother. If you see it on sale, at least half-off, I'd say it's worth that. But full price? Nope. It is a very short game, with a very set storyline, your actions do not change the ending. And I found that to be really disappointing. It was like a book you click through."
