,Recommended,259550,7678381,"Posted: 16 November, 2013",all,utopianmachine,"Although it feels like a game originally designed for the mobile platform, Hero of the Kingdom is a treat nevertheless. The story is nothing special: your home is destroyed, your father is missing, and you must track him down. Your adventure quickly becomes larger in scale, and the eventual revelations are interesting, fitting, and satisfying. The gameplay is quickly accessible, but it takes a good deal of planning and resource management to get the tools, soldiers, medicines, and weapons you'll need to overcome your many foes. There are a variety of secrets to find in the environments, so that each new map is a treasure hunt for necessary materials and wildlife.Hero of the Kingdom is a brief game and can be completed at around 5 hours. Achievements come regularly and keep you motivated. While the art style is simple, I found it charming and appropriate for this sort of adventure. I easily recommend this game for my friends who enjoy games which are a little different yet delightful."
