,Recommended,259550,26325172,"Posted: 30 October, 2016",all,Casey,"Interactive Folk Art Simulator.If you can get past the old timey graphics, this game is actually quite enjoyable. You pretty much point and click on parts of the area you are in to either (harvest resources, fight, build, buy/sell items). It is slow paced so you can progress at your leasure. One thing most people don't know is that you can actually click on things that do not necesarily have icons over them (ie: mushrooms,eggs,lobsters,crates,wood,rocks, and rarely hidden people). the cheapest method I found for sleeping is to spend 1 bread at the second zone you find. Later you can turn grain in to create flour and turn the flower in to get 6 bread (total cost 35 gold for 6 bread). Also, do not sell stuff you cannot find or harvest regularly, you may have to buy it back.If you ever see on sale for 50% off or more, i would recommend getting this relaxing interactive art book.10/10 would steal that guys wood again, only to sell it back to him."
