,Not Recommended,259550,17378440,"Posted: 3 August, 2015",all,Dr. Mr. 🇻🇮🇩🇪🇴 🇬🇦🇲🇪🇸,"In Hero of the Kingdom you click on exclamation marks to see a checklist of materials, and then you click on the various icons scattered throughout the map to collect those materials, then you click on the exclamation mark to turn-in those materials.  You will repeat this process for the next 3-4 hours until all the exclamation marks are gone.  Then you win the game.There is no strategy - you simply click what needs to be clicked.  This game is ""item management"" at its most tedious.There are no role-playing elements - labelling this game as an RPG is inaccurate, even by the loosest of definitions.There is no tension - you cannot fail any of the tasks given to you (which, again, is just gathering materials).There is no story - well, there is, but it's about as generic and shallow as a story can get.There is no gameplay - unless you're the kind of person who thinks moving rocks from one pile to another counts as a ""game"".I did not hate my time with Hero of the Kingdom, but I did not enjoy it either - it simply felt like I turned my brain off for a few hours and gained nothing from it (besides some trading cards).  If that experience appeals to you, by all means buy this game (on sale).  But if you like games with even a modicum of depth to them, you should look elsewhere."
