,Recommended,259550,13973489,"Posted: 13 January, 2015",all,webjr,"Hero of the Kingdom isn't a very involved or ""deep"" title, but the entire time I played it I had no desire to stop. Even though it isn't a turn based game it has that ""one more turn"" feel to it as you progress through the game's lovely story. It isn't a long title, and there isn't a tremendous amount of replay value, but it is definitely worth a play through at least once.The game is a point-and-click adventure that follows the story of a farm boy on what starts as a rescue mission and ends as a world saving quest. Through the entire thing you'll gather resources, hunt, fight and trade, all with simple mouse clicks. There are no mini-games to complete for any of the activities, and the game play is simplistic overall. That said, it is still enjoyable.If you're looking for a quick, narrative-based game. Hero of the Kingdom gets the job done."
