76561197996503472,Recommended,259550,9908786,"Posted: 23 April, 2014",all,Arcane Azmadi,"This isn't really an RPG- it's more a point-and-click adventure story/hidden object game. It's short,  linear and there's almost no possibility of failure. Gameplay is simply a matter of ""find obstacle, collect the items to pass obstacle, pass obstacle, rinse and repeat"". The bulk of the challenge is simply juggling the barter system to obtain the objects you need or working out how to get enough gold to proceed.That said, the game is moderately entertaining as a short-term time-waster and actually tells a surprisingly decent, if shallow, story of how your ordinary farmboy rises up to become the savior of the land. It's not original by any means, but it's very back-to-basics. If you're a completionist or achievement hound then there are a fair few challenges to kill time, but I beat it with 100% completion in about 4 hours at most (quite a lot of which was spent searching for those DAMNED last few eggs). I can't in good faith call it a ""good game"" but I don't have the heart to give it a downvote- even if plot and gameplay were both very shallow, it was cheap and it entertained me for a while and it had a peculiar charm to it. So as long as you don't expect too much, I guess I can give it a casual recommendation."
