76561197975194519,Recommended,259550,17407497,"Posted: 5 August, 2015",all,jshaffstall,"This is a terrific game!  It captures the feel of playing a typical computer RPG, but without any combat difficulties.  My daughter and I play this together, and it's a perfect casual RPG for people who don't enjoy the combat aspects of typical computer RPGs.The basic mechanism is point and click, with some hidden objects that are reminiscent of Totem Tribe.  The objects are not hidden in artificial scenes, but scattered throughout the landscape.  Actions that you can take will have prerequisites (objects you must have, for example) and you cannot take the action without meeting the prerequisites.The game is relatively short, but if combat is your least favorite part of typical RPGs, and you hate grinding to gain levels, Hero of the Kingdom is probably for you."
