76561198027433088,Recommended,259550,11548207,"Posted: 4 August, 2014",all,Grezz,"From the screenshots, I expected this to be a resource management strategy game like two of my favourites; Age of Empires or Stronghold. And in its loosest sense, I suppose it is, just incredibly simplified. See those floating yellow icons? They're little missions that you must do to acquire items or goods, or progress the story - a standard fantasy adventure with your character fighting for his father and country against ghosts, goblins and evil wizards, in order to become the titular hero. As well as clicking the yellow circles to progress, you can also find hidden items that help you on your quest, and there are achievements for finding them all.As others have said, the game can be finished in a couple of hours, but I took a leisurely ten, and enjoyed every moment! I might have felt a bit jipped at £4.99, but picked up in a sale for £1.69, I feel I easily got my money's worth. If you're looking for a casual bit of clicking and some nice scenery, you can't go far wrong."
