,Recommended,259550,30669709,Posted: 22 March,all,[BA$]Colonel_Everrage,"Basic infoGame:Hero of the KingdomGenre:Point and Click, AdventureDevelopers:Loney TroopsPrice:€6,-About the game:The game is set in a magical medieval world in which you are a farmers' son, or so you think.Your father goes on a journey and you are left to tend to the farm. At this point in the game the tutorial starts to let you do your own things. After a while the farm gets burned down by a bandit. This leaves you with no home, no tools and just a little bit of money and food. You decide to seek shelter elsewhere and leave the burned down farm. This is the beginning of your journey on which you will become the Hero of the Kingdom. Fishing, hunting and gathering your way to riches to enlist the help of hunters, knights, scouts and wizards to find your father.More technical aspects:The HUD layout is quite astethically satisfying and completely out of the way. Which is to be expected with this kind of game. I like the artwork as it leaves a lot to the imagination while simultaneously indicating what a 'creature' or character you should be imagining but not completely showing you how it looks. In short, it looks dated and a bit like Anno 1602 in some respects.Audio wise the reminder of Anno is the same. It gives a nice atmosphere and it really helped to draw me into the story.I have had several minutes of pleasure laughing at the rediculous quality of the cow's moo.My experience:I normally avoid p&c games because it is not as action packed as I like my games to be. However, the description of Hero of the Kingdom really drew me in. Seeing it was on sale for only 60 eurocents I decided to buy it and was pleasantly surprised. The story progresses well and it kind of saddened me that it was over so fast. I played for roughly two to three hours to complete the story, the last hour or two were to complete all challenges as I am quite the completionist if my mind is to it. I personally would love there to be a much bigger map and a lot more to do as it seemed to be very possible to do so and would potentially greatly improve the game. Maybe with another big questline.Pro tip:You can make an infinite amount of money by buying grain from the farm, taking that to the mill and, at the with 5 coins, creating flour. Then going back to the farm to turn it into bread and selling that to the lady in the ravine, for a hefty profit of 240 coins for every 10 bags of grain you buy.[i/]Pro'sIt will run at 1000 fps on my potato of a computerA good storyAchievements!ConsIt's very shortIt's quite linear (duh)EvaluationDo I believe this game is worth the full six euro's? No. Not a chance. Is it worth half of that? Definitely.I would highly recommend buying this while it is on sale. Expect to play it through in two to three hours tops.Overall rating: 80/100"
